criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Schoolchildren from various districts of Moscow selected as a result of questioning in
             the risk group for the development of celiac disease

          -  Availability of written informed consent of the child over 14 years of age to
             participate in the study;

          -  Availability of written informed consent of the parent of the child to participate in
             the study;

          -  Age from 7 to 18 years;

          -  Male and female gender;

          -  The number of points according to the results of the survey is more than 25.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age up to 7 years and over 18 years.

          -  The lack of written informed consent of the child over 14 years of age to participate
             in the study;

          -  The lack of written informed consent of the parent / guardian of the child to
             participate in the study;

          -  The number of points on the results of the survey from 0 to 24
